<DocsLayout title="ctx_shell — CLI Compression" description="Pattern-based compression for git, npm, cargo, docker, and TypeScript output.">
  <p>
    <code>ctx_shell</code> executes shell commands and applies pattern-based compression to the output.
    It recognizes common developer tools and strips verbose boilerplate while preserving actionable information.
  </p>
  <p>
    The same compression is also available via the <strong>shell hook</strong> (<code>lean-ctx -c command</code>),
    which compresses output transparently without requiring the LLM to use MCP tools.
  </p>

  <h2>Parameters</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>command</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Shell command to execute</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Supported Patterns</h2>

  <h3>git</h3>
  <p>Compresses <code>git status</code>, <code>git log</code>, <code>git diff</code> output. Summarizes changes into compact notation.</p>
  <pre><code>ctx_shell "git status"
→ # Branch: main [clean]
  # Modified: 2 files
  [45 tok saved (68%)]</code></pre>

  <h3>npm</h3>
  <p>Compresses <code>npm install</code>, <code>npm run</code>, <code>npm test</code> output. Removes progress bars, funding notices, and verbose dependency trees.</p>
  <pre><code>ctx_shell "npm install express"
→ +express@4.18.2 (3 deps, 847ms)
  [82 tok saved (71%)]</code></pre>

  <h3>cargo</h3>
  <p>Compresses <code>cargo build</code>, <code>cargo test</code>, <code>cargo clippy</code> output. Summarizes crate compilation, errors, and warnings.</p>

  <h3>docker</h3>
  <p>Compresses <code>docker build</code>, <code>docker ps</code> output. Summarizes steps and container listings.</p>

  <h3>TypeScript Compiler</h3>
  <p>Compresses <code>tsc</code> error output. Groups errors by file, removes redundant type paths.</p>
  <pre><code>ctx_shell "npx tsc --noEmit"
→ 3 errors in 2 files:
  auth.ts:42 TS2345 type mismatch
  db.ts:15 TS2304 name not found
  db.ts:28 TS2304 name not found</code></pre>

  <h2>Shell Hook Mode</h2>
  <p>
    Use lean-ctx as a transparent shell wrapper for automatic compression:
  </p>
  <pre><code># Single command
lean-ctx -c git status

# Shell aliases
alias git='lean-ctx -c git'
alias cargo='lean-ctx -c cargo'

# Interactive shell
lean-ctx --shell</code></pre>

  <h2>Fallback</h2>
  <p>
    For unrecognized commands, generic compression applies: removes empty lines,
    strips ANSI codes, and truncates very long output with a summary.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
